00:06:36,399 --> 00:06:40,120
Though my hair is white,
my spirit is still strong,

87
00:06:41,399 --> 00:06:45,319
my ambition for the clouds
remains unfulfilled.

88
00:06:49,439 --> 00:06:50,399
Gu,

89
00:06:51,199 --> 00:06:52,519
are you satisfied with this?

90
00:07:02,199 --> 00:07:03,800
It's finally finished.

91
00:08:11,879 --> 00:08:12,680
Gu,

92
00:08:14,079 --> 00:08:15,120
is that you?

93
00:08:17,759 --> 00:08:18,920
Indeed, it is I.

94
00:08:20,120 --> 00:08:20,959
Who might you be?

95
00:08:22,519 --> 00:08:24,160
I am Zhao Wanli.

96
00:08:27,879 --> 00:08:28,839
To meet you today

97
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:31,839
is truly my great fortune.

98
00:08:32,720 --> 00:08:33,519
Zhao!

99
00:08:34,399 --> 00:08:35,200
Gu.

100
00:08:35,639 --> 00:08:38,600
You went silent for over half a month.

101
00:08:38,960 --> 00:08:40,200
Have you been well?

102
00:08:40,799 --> 00:08:42,600
I was painting in the courtyard,

103
00:08:43,390 --> 00:08:44,679
then fell asleep in the pavilion.

104
00:08:45,279 --> 00:08:47,120
I caught a chill because of that.

105
00:08:47,799 --> 00:08:49,519
Thank you for your concern, Zhao.

106
00:08:51,039 --> 00:08:52,000
As long as you're well.

107
00:08:52,519 --> 00:08:53,720
As long as you're well.

108
00:08:58,440 --> 00:09:00,159
An Autumn Twilight Painting.

109
00:09:01,200 --> 00:09:03,279
The scenery truly is breathtaking.

110
00:09:03,799 --> 00:09:04,919
To see it today,

111
00:09:06,159 --> 00:09:07,720
I could die without regret.

112
00:09:08,919 --> 00:09:11,080
Alas, time so easily casts people aside.

113
00:09:12,919 --> 00:09:16,360
Now it is already the sun sinking
at the edge of the abyss.

114
00:09:17,200 --> 00:09:18,679
It's late into autumn.

115
00:09:18,799 --> 00:09:20,399
Gu, I must disagree.

116
00:09:21,279 --> 00:09:22,720
Liu Mengde once wrote,

117
00:09:24,120 --> 00:09:26,399
"Since ancient times,
people mourn autumn's desolation.

118
00:09:26,799 --> 00:09:29,240
I say autumn surpasses
the spring morning."

119
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:31,480
Look at today's autumn scenery.

120
00:09:32,039 --> 00:09:33,320
It's filled with autumn's colors.

121
00:09:34,039 --> 00:09:37,279
How is it any less
than the splendor of youth?

122
00:09:37,720 --> 00:09:38,519
Gu,

123
00:09:39,480 --> 00:09:41,039
your brushwork is superb.

124
00:09:45,559 --> 00:09:47,159
Look at my leg.

125
00:09:47,600 --> 00:09:49,919
I can no longer seek famous mountains,

126
00:09:50,679 --> 00:09:52,279
nor visit scenic wonders.

127
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:55,799
This painting

128
00:09:57,440 --> 00:09:59,960
was done beside
a ruined pond in my courtyard,

129
00:10:00,519 --> 00:10:03,519
painted after broken stones
and withered trees.

130
00:10:04,360 --> 00:10:06,159
I have long been trapped in here.

131
00:10:09,639 --> 00:10:10,519
I'm of no use anymore.

132
00:10:10,759 --> 00:10:12,720
Gu, that is even more mistaken.

133
00:10:13,879 --> 00:10:15,360
When I was young,

134
00:10:15,660 --> 00:10:17,000
a mountain was simply a mountain.

135
00:10:18,279 --> 00:10:19,840
After years of life,

136
00:10:20,190 --> 00:10:21,679
a mountain was no longer a mountain,

137
00:10:22,080 --> 00:10:23,399
as though lost in mist.

138
00:10:23,960 --> 00:10:25,080
And now, Gu,

139
00:10:25,279 --> 00:10:26,679
to be able to paint,

140
00:10:27,039 --> 00:10:29,159
from a ruined pond, such beauty,

141
00:10:30,600 --> 00:10:32,440
it turns out a mountain is
still a mountain,

142
00:10:32,879 --> 00:10:34,879
only that it is no longer the same one.

143
00:10:35,559 --> 00:10:37,080
You've long surpassed

144
00:10:37,080 --> 00:10:39,919
that youth who once
trusted only his soaring brush.

145
00:10:48,080 --> 00:10:50,519
Zhao, you truly understand me.

146
00:10:52,159 --> 00:10:53,159
It was not in vain

147
00:10:54,480 --> 00:10:56,799
that fate allowed you and me to meet.

148
00:11:04,639 --> 00:11:06,879
The storm over Jiang City has passed,

149
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:10,919
by dusk, brush and ink turn cool.

150
00:11:13,360 --> 00:11:15,390
Though my hair is white,
my spirit is still strong,

151
00:11:15,720 --> 00:11:17,919
my ambition for the clouds
remains unfulfilled.

152
00:11:22,879 --> 00:11:23,679
Zhao.

153
00:11:25,320 --> 00:11:27,240
At my age now,

154
00:11:28,039 --> 00:11:29,639
with nothing to my name,

155
00:11:31,840 --> 00:11:33,720
can my spirit still be strong?

156
00:11:34,080 --> 00:11:37,120
In my lifetime, I have seen countless
works of calligraphy and painting.

157
00:11:38,039 --> 00:11:40,759
Yet among them all,

158
00:11:41,080 --> 00:11:42,960
only your paintings are
my greatest love.

159
00:11:43,600 --> 00:11:46,639
I believe that
if your heart remains strong,

160
00:11:47,200 --> 00:11:49,000
your name will endure through the ages,

161
00:11:49,080 --> 00:11:50,559
never fading away!

162
00:11:55,840 --> 00:11:58,480
All my life, I, Gu Zhiqian,

163
00:11:59,639 --> 00:12:01,320
chased fame and glory,

164
00:12:02,200 --> 00:12:03,759
and squandered my youth.

165
00:12:06,039 --> 00:12:08,360
Worse still,
I failed those who loved me.

166
00:12:11,240 --> 00:12:13,120
I once thought that my life

167
00:12:14,480 --> 00:12:16,679
would amount to nothing at all.

168
00:12:18,679 --> 00:12:19,759
But I never expected

169
00:12:21,360 --> 00:12:24,080
to meet a confidant like you, Zhao.

170
00:12:25,639 --> 00:12:27,840
As long as even
one true confidant remains,

171
00:12:28,679 --> 00:12:30,039
then I, Gu Zhiqian,

172
00:12:31,738 --> 00:12:34,600
have not lived this life in vain.

173
00:12:36,480 --> 00:12:37,399
Zhao,

174
00:12:39,840 --> 00:12:40,879
thank you.

175
00:12:50,519 --> 00:12:51,360
Zhao Wanli!

176
00:12:51,440 --> 00:12:52,320
Gu!

177
00:12:52,519 --> 00:12:53,440
Gu!

178
00:12:54,480 --> 00:12:55,879
You're finally awake.

179
00:12:59,879 --> 00:13:00,679
Why…

180
00:13:01,519 --> 00:13:02,799
Why am I here?

181
00:13:02,840 --> 00:13:03,919
You reckless fool.

182
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:05,279
I told you not to drink so much.

183
00:13:05,279 --> 00:13:06,559
You'll drink yourself to death!

184
00:13:06,600 --> 00:13:07,720
You weren't breathing.

185
00:13:07,720 --> 00:13:09,080
I called, but you wouldn't wake up.

186
00:13:09,090 --> 00:13:09,960
I thought…

187
00:13:12,120 --> 00:13:12,919
I thought…

188
00:13:16,919 --> 00:13:18,840
You nearly scared me to death.

189
00:13:20,639 --> 00:13:21,240
Alright.

190
00:13:22,200 --> 00:13:23,080
Don't cry now.

191
00:13:23,279 --> 00:13:24,159
Don't cry.

192
00:13:28,000 --> 00:13:29,240
I beg you,

193
00:13:29,240 --> 00:13:30,480
please don't cry.

194
00:13:30,480 --> 00:13:31,159
Alright?

195
00:13:33,440 --> 00:13:34,240
You…

196
00:13:36,440 --> 00:13:37,240
Don't cry.

197
00:13:38,039 --> 00:13:39,759
I'm perfectly fine, see?

198
00:13:49,519 --> 00:13:50,360
Don't cry.

199
00:13:50,440 --> 00:13:51,240
Don't cry.

200
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:54,360
You absolute fool.

201
00:13:54,559 --> 00:13:56,000
I was so worried!

202
00:13:56,000 --> 00:13:57,679
You fool!

203
00:13:57,960 --> 00:13:58,799
I'm a fool.

204
00:13:59,000 --> 00:13:59,840
I'm a fool.

205
00:14:06,039 --> 00:14:06,799
I'm a fool.

206
00:14:07,399 --> 00:14:09,120
I've let you down all these years.

207
00:14:10,639 --> 00:14:11,600
I'm a fool

208
00:14:13,000 --> 00:14:14,240
for making you wait until now.

209
00:14:15,440 --> 00:14:17,720
I was a fool for thinking
only of my own prospects

210
00:14:18,159 --> 00:14:19,759
and freedom.

211
00:14:21,300 --> 00:14:22,519
In the end, I've let you down.

212
00:14:27,720 --> 00:14:29,180
What nonsense are you talking about?

213
00:14:29,960 --> 00:14:30,720
Zhou'er.

214
00:14:31,000 --> 00:14:31,600
Zhou'er.

215
00:14:31,720 --> 00:14:32,480
Zhou'er.

216
00:14:37,440 --> 00:14:39,639
Just now, a friend of mine told me

217
00:14:40,279 --> 00:14:41,720
that he spent his life chasing fame,

218
00:14:42,799 --> 00:14:44,159
only to squander his youth,

219
00:14:45,240 --> 00:14:46,720
and let those who loved him down.

220
00:14:46,840 --> 00:14:48,320
Now, he regrets it.

221
00:14:50,519 --> 00:14:52,200
I don't want to repeat his mistake.

222
00:14:54,480 --> 00:14:55,519
I want to be with you.

223
00:14:55,799 --> 00:14:56,840
Stop talking.

224
00:14:57,840 --> 00:14:59,679
I'm not ready yet.

225
00:15:00,600 --> 00:15:01,480
Alright.

226
00:15:01,960 --> 00:15:03,279
It was too sudden.

227
00:15:03,279 --> 00:15:04,399
It really was.

228
00:15:05,639 --> 00:15:06,559
From this day on,

229
00:15:08,200 --> 00:15:09,240
I'll treat you well.

230
00:15:11,080 --> 00:15:12,100
I'll do good where I can,

231
00:15:12,700 --> 00:15:13,879
and not ask about the future.

232
00:15:15,840 --> 00:15:16,639
How's that?

233
00:15:20,799 --> 00:15:21,600
You're smiling.

234
00:15:22,320 --> 00:15:23,159
That's good.

235
00:15:23,799 --> 00:15:24,679
That's good.

236
00:15:25,840 --> 00:15:26,279
Come.

237
00:15:27,080 --> 00:15:28,159
I promise you,

238
00:15:28,759 --> 00:15:30,240
I'll never drink again.

239
00:15:31,559 --> 00:15:33,279
All that wine was a family heirloom.

240
00:15:33,679 --> 00:15:35,919
My father saved it back then,
thinking I'd marry one day.

241
00:15:35,919 --> 00:15:37,159
You drank it all dry.

242
00:15:37,960 --> 00:15:39,159
There's not even a drop left.

243
00:15:39,159 --> 00:15:39,600
Yes.

244
00:15:42,200 --> 00:15:43,840
Not a single jug left.

245
00:15:44,159 --> 00:15:45,600
Not even a drop?

246
00:15:45,879 --> 00:15:47,679
You just promised
you wouldn't drink again.

247
00:15:47,879 --> 00:15:48,919
You fool.

248
00:15:48,919 --> 00:15:49,879
You're a cursed fool!

249
00:15:49,879 --> 00:15:50,480
My dear,

250
00:15:50,679 --> 00:15:51,799
I was just joking.

251
00:15:51,879 --> 00:15:52,720
Just kidding.

252
00:15:53,679 --> 00:15:54,879
I won't drink again. Never.

253
00:16:00,840 --> 00:16:02,720
I've drunk the wine
meant for your marriage,

254
00:16:03,440 --> 00:16:04,720
then you belong to me.

255
00:16:05,759 --> 00:16:08,399
Isn't that simply fate at work?

256
00:16:11,159 --> 00:16:12,799
Who says we're a match made by heaven?

257
00:16:15,480 --> 00:16:16,000
My dear.

258
00:16:16,240 --> 00:16:16,799
My dear!

259
00:16:24,159 --> 00:16:24,919
Coming.

260
00:16:27,840 --> 00:16:28,759
Scholar Zhao is here.

261
00:16:28,840 --> 00:16:29,519
I came.

262
00:16:41,320 --> 00:16:43,279
An Autumn Gift to a Friend.

263
00:16:50,120 --> 00:16:51,919
This is Gu's original work.

264
00:16:54,120 --> 00:16:55,399
Gu painted me.

265
00:16:57,240 --> 00:16:58,480
Not just you.

266
00:16:58,799 --> 00:16:59,679
He also said

267
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:02,279
you were the only
true confidant of his life.

268
00:17:06,079 --> 00:17:06,880
You two...

269
00:17:07,359 --> 00:17:08,480
How did you know?

270
00:17:09,119 --> 00:17:10,599
Well, you never told us

271
00:17:10,920 --> 00:17:13,079
how you became his confidant.

272
00:17:18,720 --> 00:17:19,559
May I

273
00:17:20,559 --> 00:17:21,680
keep this painting?

274
00:17:22,079 --> 00:17:22,720
Of course.

275
00:17:23,119 --> 00:17:23,759
Thank you.

276
00:17:24,200 --> 00:17:24,799
Thank you.

277
00:17:25,039 --> 00:17:25,920
To be honest,

278
00:17:26,799 --> 00:17:29,440
we've already uncovered the secret
of the Autumn Twilight Painting.

279
00:17:30,400 --> 00:17:33,079
We understand
the bond between you and Gu.

280
00:17:34,000 --> 00:17:36,400
But the Liangzhu silk used
for the Autumn Twilight Painting

281
00:17:36,720 --> 00:17:38,160
once belonged to a friend of ours.

282
00:17:38,440 --> 00:17:39,720
That bond,

283
00:17:40,079 --> 00:17:41,480
we hope you'll honor as well.

